# PURPOSE

This document is the single source of truth for Project Atlas.

Every implementation task, prompt, feature request, and development decision must align with this document.

This document exists to:

• Keep development organized.
• Prevent duplicate work.
• Maintain architectural consistency.
• Prioritize features based on release value.
• Minimize wasted implementation tasks.
• Track overall progress from concept to Version 1.0 Release.

====================================================================

# PRODUCT VISION

Atlas is an autonomous AI operating system for inventors.

Atlas is not a chatbot.

Atlas is not a project management application.

Atlas is not simply an assistant.

Atlas functions as an AI company.

Each department performs real work, collaborates with other departments, produces deliverables, and only escalates decisions that require human approval.

The founder should spend time making important decisions—not managing individual tasks.

====================================================================

# PRODUCT PRINCIPLES

The following principles are permanent.

1. Atlas performs work instead of simply providing advice.

2. Every department must produce measurable outputs.

3. Atlas never asks the founder to perform work it can perform itself.

4. Human interaction is limited to:
   • strategic decisions
   • legal approvals
   • physical-world actions
   • external relationships

5. Every completed department must create structured outputs for downstream departments.

6. Atlas should automatically continue work whenever dependencies are satisfied.

7. Placeholder states should only exist when absolutely unavoidable.

8. Every new feature must move Atlas closer to a fully autonomous inventor operating system.

