# DEPARTMENT RULES

Every department must define:

Purpose

Inputs

Processing

Outputs

Dependencies

Completion Criteria

No department is considered complete unless it produces useful work products.

====================================================================

# TASK RULES

Every implementation task must answer YES to all of the following:

Does this move Atlas closer to release?

Does this remove technical debt?

Does this unblock additional departments?

Does this improve autonomous execution?

Can this be tested immediately?

If the answer is NO, the task should be postponed unless it fixes a critical issue.

====================================================================

# DAILY DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW

Step 1

Review this document.

Step 2

Identify the first unfinished milestone.

Step 3

Implement only that milestone unless instructed otherwise.

Step 4

Do not redesign completed systems.

Step 5

Preserve architecture.

Step 6

Run tests.

Step 7

Report:

• completed work

• files changed

• tests

• remaining blockers

